	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001584_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="center">Fever Powder</p>
<lb/><p>Take of Resin of Jalap 
<lb/>and Calomel of each eight grains 
<lb/>Quinine &amp; Rhubarba of each 
<lb/>four grains - mix well together, 
<lb/>and when needed, make into 
<lb/>pills with spirit of cardamoms<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Dose from (10) ten to (20) twenty 
<lb/>grains. The mixture keeps 
<lb/>best in powder.</p>
<lb/><p>If the violent symptoms 
<lb/>are not relieved in from four 
<lb/>to six hours by the operation 
<lb/>of the pills a dessert spoonful 
<lb/>of Epsom salts may be taken<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Then quinine in four or six 
<lb/>grain doses completes the cure<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>It is usually given till the ears 
<lb/>ring or deafness is produced<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p><placeName>Tette</placeName> 26<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi></p>
<lb/><p>1860</p>
			
